General build instructions:

  1. If you are building from cloned Git repository, you will need to update
     the git submodules. You can do this when cloning with:
     
     $ git clone --recursive https://github.com/khaledhosny/ots.git;
     
     Or with an existing repository with:
     
     $ git submodule init;
     $ git submodule update;
     
  2. Run autoreconf. A convenience script is provided:

     $ ./autogen.sh

  3. Build OTS

     $ ./configure
     $ make

  4. Run the tests (if you wish)

     $ make check

Building on Windows:

   1. A POSIX-compatible environment is required to build OTS, MSYS2 is
      recommended. Follow the installation instructions on
	  https://msys2.github.io/.

   2. Install the required packages:

      $ pacman -S autoconf automake pkg-config gcc make zlib-devel

   3. Follow the general build instructions above.
